5. Obligations of the Licensee

The grant of the rights mentioned above is subject to some restrictions and obligations imposed on the Licensee.
Those obligations are the following:

Attribution right: The Licensee shall keep intact all copyright, patent or trademarks notices and all notices
that refer to the Licence and to the disclaimer of warranties. The Licensee must include a copy of such notices
and a copy of the Licence with every copy of the Work or Derivative Works distributed or communicated by the Licensee.
The Licensee must cause any Derivative Work to carry prominent notices stating that the Work has been modified
and the date of modification.

Copyleft Mechanism: If the Licensee distributes or communicates copies of the Original Works or Derivative Works
based upon the Original Work, this Distribution or Communication will be done under the terms of this Licence or
under a later version of this Licence, unless the Original Work is expressly distributed only under this version
of the Licence — for example by the communication of "EUPL v. 1.2 only". The Licensee (becoming Licensor) cannot
offer or impose any additional terms or conditions on the Work or Derivative Work that alter or restrict the terms
of the Licence.

However, the Licensee may add to the Work or a Derivative Work a licence compatible with this Licence, provided
that such licence does not contradict the copyleft mechanism of this Licence. The Licensee may also distribute
Work under a new EUPL version, but only if the new version is substantially similar to this version and in any case
permits to distribute and sublicense the Work under the same conditions as this Licence.

Compatibility clause: If the Work contains a notice stating that it is subject to a EUPL-incompatible licence,
or is made subject to such a licence, the Licensor shall add to the copyright notice declaring his authorisation
to license under this version of the EUPL or have the choice, by communicating with the Licensor, to see the Work
(possibly as a Derivative Work) governed by this Licence instead of the licence indicated.

In case of a dispute about the compatibility of a licence, the decision to check the compatibility of licences
will be the responsibility of the court having jurisdiction according to Article 15 of this Licence.

Source Code: The Licensor may provide the Work in Source Code form or as Executable Code. If it is provided
as Executable Code, the Licensor shall provide in addition a machine-readable copy of the Source Code of the Work
or indicate in a notice following the copyright notice that the Source Code is freely available.

Integrity of the Work: Any Licensee who authorises the further distribution of the Work or Derivative Works is
required to pass on or make available information that enables the recipients to identify both the original Work
and its modifications clearly. This is intended to ensure that the integrity of the Work is maintained.

